the organizers of that,

01:32:16.680 --> 01:32:18.040
otherwise very good week,

01:32:18.820 --> 01:32:20.920
had made the gasky error

01:32:20.920 --> 01:32:22.780
of putting it into a Tampant Hotel,

01:32:24.380 --> 01:32:27.560
and the lady who ran it

01:32:27.560 --> 01:32:30.180
was a well-appearance chemical type,

01:32:30.600 --> 01:32:33.820
and Mark and I

01:32:33.820 --> 01:32:36.580
arrived home one night about two,

01:32:37.080 --> 01:32:38.340
one morning about two,

01:32:39.000 --> 01:32:40.200
and we had forgotten our keys,

01:32:41.060 --> 01:32:44.580
and I remember very well that last walk up to the hotel,

01:32:45.140 --> 01:32:49.480
because we tipped into and against each other at every step,

01:32:50.100 --> 01:32:53.220
and it was strange this sequence bumping in detail,

01:32:53.420 --> 01:32:55.160
which went on the whole way along that street,

01:32:55.300 --> 01:32:56.580
but we couldn't help it.

01:32:57.660 --> 01:32:58.780
We got to the hotel,

01:32:58.900 --> 01:33:01.640
and one of these places made up of

01:33:01.640 --> 01:33:04.040
what had formerly been a role of private houses,

01:33:04.840 --> 01:33:05.940
all joined together,

01:33:06.760 --> 01:33:09.100
and all the entrances seated up tight,

01:33:10.080 --> 01:33:12.220
except the one which was first used to the hotel,

01:33:12.980 --> 01:33:14.700
and Mark and I hadn't our keys,

01:33:14.800 --> 01:33:16.200
but we tried all the other doors,

01:33:16.400 --> 01:33:17.740
any of which hadn't been open for years,

01:33:17.740 --> 01:33:19.160
but we didn't have the faces

01:33:19.580 --> 01:33:21.700
later on in the pub or the hotel,

01:33:22.460 --> 01:33:25.360
and finally had to move to Gore,

01:33:25.520 --> 01:33:26.780
