01:33:27.720 --> 01:33:30.500
and pulled us off very, very severely,

01:33:31.920 --> 01:33:34.060
so that was a good time that week,

01:33:34.640 --> 01:33:38.540
but it was hard, and she wasn't going to put up with people who drank a lot,

01:33:39.720 --> 01:33:41.780
because they're having like that in her premises.

01:33:44.440 --> 01:33:46.020
And the next day,

01:33:46.160 --> 01:33:47.440
that was the fourth day of the week,

01:33:47.980 --> 01:33:48.780
Jim was arriving,

01:33:50.200 --> 01:33:53.180
and I was told into the owner of the hotel,

01:33:53.720 --> 01:33:55.100
Arkham and Lobby, and Jim,

01:33:55.660 --> 01:33:59.580
he decided to go into part two of the telling off,

01:34:00.140 --> 01:34:01.500
and to really go on and on,

01:34:01.540 --> 01:34:03.320
but she didn't like the losers,

01:34:03.560 --> 01:34:05.080
and this is a tempered heart,

01:34:05.220 --> 01:34:09.040
and then just that moment Jim came into the hall,

01:34:09.040 --> 01:34:11.040
and he was bit tired,

01:34:11.140 --> 01:34:12.260
he had travelled up from London,

01:34:12.920 --> 01:34:14.640
and he was wearing a black coat

01:34:14.640 --> 01:34:19.480
and a black pole neck shirt,

01:34:19.940 --> 01:34:22.020
and his fur hat pulled down,

01:34:22.480 --> 01:34:24.720
and he looked remarkably aesthetic,

01:34:25.320 --> 01:34:30.000
and the aunt lady looked at him and said,

01:34:30.280 --> 01:34:31.320
is this Mr. Brish?

01:34:31.520 --> 01:34:32.960
I said yes, that's Mr. Brish,

01:34:33.300 --> 01:34:35.200
and said, is he a minister?

01:34:37.660 --> 01:34:38.640
I said no,

01:34:38.820 --> 01:34:41.840
but he has written books with the outlawedliest religion,

01:34:42.900 --> 01:34:45.240
and I just lit up with this auntie,

01:34:45.580 --> 01:34:46.980
bashed across the lobby,

01:34:48.180 --> 01:34:50.360
and said, Mr. Brish, come with me,

01:34:50.420 --> 01:34:51.480
and I'll get you a key,

01:34:52.180 --> 01:34:53.700
and she went to Bathway,

01:34:53.860 --> 01:34:55.320
and he put her hands up and said,

01:34:55.920 --> 01:34:57.540
can you get a drink here anywhere?

01:35:00.460 --> 01:35:03.920
I said, can you, there are not even one of us,

01:35:05.780 --> 01:35:10.120
and that's a sad and lonely aspect of Jim's character.

01:35:10.700 --> 01:35:12.740
I appreciate all of our suggestions much,

01:35:14.140 --> 01:35:18.120
but it's been covered very adequately by other speakers,

01:35:18.920 --> 01:35:21.660
so I'll stand by, thank you.

